==Legacy==

Opinions on Gorbachev are deeply divided.{{sfn|Taubman|2017|p=1}} Many, particularly in Western countries, see him as the greatest statesman of the second half of the twentieth century.{{sfn|Taubman|2017|p=1}} In September 1990 [[U.S. Secretary of State]] [[James Baker]] told him "nobody in the world has ever tried what you and your supporters are trying today...I've seen a lot, but I've never met a politician with as much bravery and courage as you have."<ref>[[Richard Rhodes]], "Arsenals of Folly: The Making of the Nuclear Arms Race," (New York: Vintage Books, 2007), p. 296</ref> In Russia, he is widely despised for his role in the collapse of the Soviet Union and the ensuing economic collapse.{{sfn|Taubman|2017|p=1}} During his career, Gorbachev attracted the admiration of some colleagues, but others came to hate him.{{sfn|Taubman|2017|p=134}}

=== Honours and accolades ===
[[File:President Reagan presents Reagan Freedom Medal to Mikhail Gorbachev at Library.jpg|thumb|right|Former President of the United States [[Ronald Reagan]] awards Gorbachev the first ever [[Ronald Reagan Freedom Award]] at the [[Ronald Reagan Presidential Library|Reagan Library]], 4 May 1992]]

==== Soviet Union and Russia decorations ====
* [[Order of St. Andrew]] (2011), the highest state decoration of Russia, awarded for work during [[USSR]] leadership
* [[Order of Honour (Russian Federation)|Order of Honour]] (2001)
* [[Order of Lenin]] (1971, 1973, 1981)
* [[Order of October Revolution]] (1978)
* [[Order of the Badge of Honour]] (1966)
* [[Order of the Red Banner of Labour]] (1947). He was awarded when he was only 16 and was one of the youngest recipients of the award.
* [[Medal "For Labour Valour"]]
* [[Medal "For Strengthening Military Cooperation"]]
* [[Medal "In Commemoration of the 1500th Anniversary of Kiev"]]
* [[Jubilee Medal "Forty Years of Victory in the Great Patriotic War 1941–1945"]]

==== Foreign decorations and awards ====
*In 1987, Gorbachev was awarded the [[Indira Gandhi Prize]] from [[Government of India]].
*In 1989, Gorbachev was awarded the [[Otto Hahn Peace Medal]] in Gold of the United Nations Association of Germany (DGVN) in Berlin for "his contributions to nuclear disarmament of the great powers and the creation of a fundamentally new political order in Europe".
*In 1990, Gorbachev was awarded the [[Nobel Peace Prize]] for "his leading role in the peace process which today characterizes important parts of the international community".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/peace/laureates/1990/press.html |title=The Nobel Peace Prize 1990 |publisher=Nobelprize.org |date=15 October 1990 |accessdate=3 November 2010}}</ref>
*On 4 May 1992, Gorbachev was awarded the first ever [[Ronald Reagan Freedom Award]] at the [[Ronald Reagan Presidential Library]] in [[Simi Valley]], California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reaganfoundation.org/programs/cpa/awards.asp |title=Ronald Reagan Presidential Foundation & Library |accessdate=24 February 2007 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080610173410/http://www.reaganfoundation.org/programs/cpa/awards.asp |archivedate=10 June 2008 |df=dmy}}</ref>
*On 6 May 1992, Gorbachev was awarded the honorary degree of Doctor of Laws from [[Westminster College (Missouri)|Westminster College]] in [[Fulton, Missouri|Fulton]], Missouri.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.churchillmemorial.org/lecture/green/Pages/MikhailGorbachev.aspx |title=National Churchill Museum &#124; Mikhail Gorbachev Lecture at the National Churchill Museum |publisher=Churchillmemorial.org |date=6 May 1992 |accessdate=19 November 2012}}</ref>
*In 1993 Gorbachev was awarded a Legum Doctor, ''honoris causa'' from [[Carleton University]] in Ottawa, Canada. He was also given an honorary degree from The [[University of Calgary]] in Calgary, Alberta, Canada.<ref>{{Cite press release|first=Andrew|last=Wark|publisher=University of Calgary|title=Mikhail Gorbachev to present U of C public lecture|url=https://www.ucalgary.ca/uofc/events/unicomm/NewsReleases/gorby00.htm|date=18 September 2000|accessdate=10 September 2013}}</ref> In the same year, he was conferred with the [[Freedom of the City of Aberdeen]].

[[File:Michail Gorbatschow BE1.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Gorbachev on 12 March 2013]]
*Gorbachev was the 1994 recipient of the [[Grawemeyer Award]] for ideas improving world order, awarded by the [[University of Louisville]], Kentucky.<ref name=grawemeyer.org>{{cite web|title=1994– Mikhail Gorbachev|url=http://grawemeyer.org/worldorder/previous-winners/1994-mikhail-gorbachev.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111013203704/http://grawemeyer.org/worldorder/previous-winners/1994-mikhail-gorbachev.html|archivedate=13 October 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
*In 1995, Gorbachev received an Honorary Doctorate from [[Durham University]], County Durham, England for his contribution to "the cause of political tolerance and an end to Cold War-style confrontation".<ref>[http://www.dur.ac.uk/university.calendar/volumei/honorary_degrees/ Honorary Degrees]. dur.ac.uk</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dur.ac.uk/committees/Council/1995-11-28m |title=Minutes of the Council Meeting |publisher=Durham University |accessdate=8 September 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111119050846/http://www.dur.ac.uk/committees/Council/1995-11-28m |archivedate=19 November 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
*In 1995 he was awarded the Grand-Cross of the [[Order of Liberty]] by Portuguese President [[Mário Soares]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ordens.presidencia.pt/?idc=154&list=1|title=CIDADÃOS ESTRANGEIROS AGRACIADOS COM ORDENS PORTUGUESAS - Página Oficial das Ordens Honoríficas Portuguesas|website=www.ordens.presidencia.pt|language=pt|access-date=7 August 2017}}</ref>
*For his historic role in the evolution of ''[[glasnost]]'', and for his leadership in the disarmament negotiations with the United States during the [[Presidency of Ronald Reagan|Reagan administration]], Gorbachev was awarded the Courage of Conscience award 20 October 1996.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://peaceabbey.org/awards/cocrecipientlist.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080216030548/http://peaceabbey.org/awards/cocrecipientlist.html |archivedate=16 February 2008 |title=The Peace Abbey Courage of Conscience Recipients List |publisher=Peaceabbey.org |date=20 November 2005 |accessdate=3 November 2010}}</ref>
* In 1998, Gorbachev received the Freedom Award from the [[National Civil Rights Museum]] in [[Memphis, Tennessee]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.civilrightsmuseum.org/Freedom-Awards-Winners.aspx#sthash.eEo0oFeS.dpbs |title=Archived copy |accessdate=28 February 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140330065715/http://civilrightsmuseum.org/Freedom-Awards-Winners.aspx |archivedate=30 March 2014 |df=dmy}}</ref>
* In 2002, Gorbachev received the [[Freedom of the City of Dublin]] from the [[Dublin City Council]], the [[Capital of Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dublincity.ie/main-menu-your-council-lord-mayor-about-lord-mayor-freedom-city/previous-recipients-keys-city|title=Previous Recipients of Keys to the City {{!}} Dublin City Council|website=www.dublincity.ie|language=en|access-date=14 December 2017}}</ref>
*In 2002, Gorbachev received an honorary degree of a Doctor in Laws (LL.D.) "in recognition of his political service and contribution to peace" from [[Trinity College, Dublin]], Ireland.<ref name="Tcd.ie">{{cite web|url=http://www.tcd.ie/Secretary/Communications/Press_Releases/PRArchive/PR0102/PRGorbachev.html |title=Trinity College Honours Mikhail Gorbachev |publisher=Tcd.ie |accessdate=3 November 2010}}</ref>
*In 2002, Gorbachev was awarded the [[Charles V European Award|Charles V Prize]] by the European Academy of Yuste Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fundacionyuste.org/en/project/mijail-gorbachov/|title=Mikhail Gorbachev|publisher=European Academy of Yuste Foundation|accessdate=16 September 2017}}</ref>
*Gorbachev, together with [[Bill Clinton]] and [[Sophia Loren]], were awarded the [[46th Annual Grammy Awards|2004 Grammy Award]] for [[Grammy Award for Best Spoken Word Album for Children|Best Spoken Word Album for Children]] for their recording of [[Sergei Prokofiev]]'s ''[[Peter and the Wolf]]'' for [[Pentatone (record label)|PENTATONE.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pentatonemusic.com/peter-and-the-wolf-wolf-tracks|title=Prokofiev Peter and the Wolf – Beintus Wolf Tracks|website=pentatonemusic|access-date=18 December 2016}}</ref>
*In 2005, Gorbachev was awarded the Point Alpha Prize for his role in supporting [[German reunification]]. He also received an honorary doctorate from the [[University of Münster]].<ref name="Deutsche Welle">{{cite web|url = http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,1619484,00.html|title = Reunification Politicians Accept Prize|publisher=Deutsche Welle|accessdate =22 May 2006}}</ref>
*In 2011, Gorbachev was awarded a ''honoris causa'' doctorate from [[University of Liège]] in [[Liège]], Belgium.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ulg.ac.be/cms/c_1252318/en/mikhail-gorbachev-a-ulg-honorary-doctorate|title=Université de Liège – Mikhail Gorbachev, a ULg Honorary Doctorate|work=ULg|accessdate=29 October 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141029181131/http://www.ulg.ac.be/cms/c_1252318/en/mikhail-gorbachev-a-ulg-honorary-doctorate|archivedate=29 October 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

