{{update|date=July 2018}}
'''Serkan Golge''' (Serkan Gölge) is a Turkish-American scientist who is currently imprisoned in [[Turkey]]. He worked as a full-time [[NASA]] contractor on NASA's proposed [[manned mission to Mars]]<ref name="foreignpolicy">{{cite web|last1=Bohn|first1=Lauren|last2=Tekerek|first2=Tugba|title=On a Mission to Mars, Imprisoned in Turkey|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2017/06/30/on-a-mission-to-mars-imprisoned-in-turkey/|website=Foreign Policy|accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref> with an office next to the [[Christopher_C._Kraft_Jr._Mission_Control_Center| Mission Control Center]].{{cn|date=October 2018}} He graduated from [[Fatih University]] and received his [[Ph.D.]] in [[physics]] from [[Old Dominion University]] in 2010. He became a [[naturalization|naturalized]] US citizen the same year.<ref name="foreignpolicy"/><ref>{{cite web|last1=Golge|first1=Serkan|title=Turkey's jailed NASA scientist now sees the sun just one hour a day|url=https://turkeypurge.com/turkeys-jailed-nasa-scientist-now-sees-the-sun-just-one-hour-a-day/|website=Turkey Purge|accessdate=13 October 2017}}</ref>
Golge was arrested by the Turkish government on July 23, 2016, on charges of participating in terrorism and conspiring against the government as a member of the [[Gülen movement]], which Turkey designates the "Fethullahist Terrorist Organization." As evidence the prosecution presented a 1 $ bill found in his apartment (which by prosecutors often is presented as evidence that someone is linked to the Gülen Movement), the fact that he had a bank account at a bank linked to the Gülen movement and that he has studied at a university linked to the Gülen Movement.<ref>https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2018/02/turkish-american-nasa-scientist-sentenced-75-years-prison</ref> Golge denied being a member of the Gülen movement or undertaking any anti-government activities. On February 8, 2018, he was sentenced to 7.5 years in prison.<ref>{{cite web|last=McTighe |first=Kristen |url=http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2018/02/turkish-american-nasa-scientist-sentenced-75-years-prison |title=Turkish-American NASA scientist sentenced to 7.5 years in prison &#124; Science &#124; AAAS |publisher=Sciencemag.org |date=2018-07-13 |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> The government in Ankara believes that the Gülen movement is at least partially responsible for the [[2016 Turkish coup d'état attempt]] and has arrested many of its members, followers and sympathizers, and suspected sympathizers, members and followers since the coup's failure in July 2016. Suspected conspirators have included judges, academics, and journalists.<ref>{{cite web|author=Susan Katz Keating |url=https://aminewswire.com/stories/510996151-american-nasa-scientist-held-by-erdogan-turkish-media-says |title=AMI Newswire |publisher=AMI Newswire |date=2016-08-17 |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|title=Turkey's Purge|url=http://www.turkeypurge.com|website=Turkey Purge|accessdate=17 Oct 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://physicstoday.scitation.org/do/10.1063/PT.5.1082/full |title= NASA scientist detained in Turkey following failed coup |date= August 16, 2016 |publisher=Physics Today |accessdate= June 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://kristof.blogs.nytimes.com/2017/03/20/a-nasa-scientist-has-been-imprisoned-in-turkey-for-8-months |title= A NASA scientist has been imprisoned in Turkey for 8 months |date= March 20, 2017 |publisher=NY Times |accessdate= June 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/how-did-a-nasa-scientist-get-in-turkish-prison |title= How did a NASA scientist get in Turkish prison |date= March 25, 2017 |publisher=The Daily Beast |accessdate= June 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dailycaller.com/2017/03/27/nasa-scientist-still-being-held-in-turkish-prison-as-spy |title= NASA scientist still being held in Turkish prison as spy |date= March 27, 2017 |publisher=Daily Caller |accessdate= June 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.houstonpress.com/news/nasa-johnson-space-center-scientist-detained-in-turkey-over-single-american-dollar-bill-9299043 |title= NASA Johnson Space Center scientist detained in Turkey over single American dollar bill |date= March 29, 2017 |publisher=Houston Press |accessdate= June 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://dailycaller.com/2017/04/18/turkey-postpones-trial-of-nasa-scientist-arrested-for-possessing-a-1-bill |title= Turkey postpones trial of NASA scientist arrested for possessing a $1 bill |date= April 18, 2017 |publisher=Daily Caller |accessdate= June 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.houstonpress.com/news/johnson-space-center-scientist-detained-in-turkey-denied-bail-9363839 |title= Johnson Space Center scientist detained in Turkey denied bail |date= April 18, 2017 |publisher=Houston Press |accessdate= June 14, 2017}}</ref>
